The area of this region formed by six congruent squares is 294 square centimeters. What is the perimeter of the region, in centimeters?
\begin{center}
\begin{asy}
size(8cm);
draw((0,0)--(-10,0)--(-10,10)--(0,10)--cycle);
draw((0,10)--(0,20)--(-30,20)--(-30,10)--cycle);
draw((-10,10)--(-10,20));
draw((-20,10)--(-20,20));
draw((-20,20)--(-20,30)--(-40,30)--(-40,20)--cycle);
draw((-30,20)--(-30,30));
\end{asy}
\end{center}
}

\textbf{Answer:} Since $MC = 8$ and $M$ is the midpoint of $\overline{BC}$, we have $MB=MC = 8$, so $BC=8+8=16$. Since $B$ and $C$ trisect $\overline{AD}$, we have $AB = CD = BC = 16$, so $AD =16+16+16=\boxed{48}$.
